The paper discusses the use of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) for natural language processing tasks such as sentiment analysis, question answering, and machine translation. These tasks are typically associated with the arXiv CS sub-categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper focuses on using RNNs for Ontology Learning, which falls under the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Semantic Web (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, and cs.SI.
